title: Parliament House, Canberra evacuated as smoke fills the corridors
description: The entire Senate wing of Parliament House in Canberra has been evacuated due to smoke in the corridors.

title: Furious drivers baffled by parking apps plead with firms to let them deal with a human
description: It comes after the Mail revealed how more than two million drivers will soon live in 'parking meter deserts' as pay and display machines are increasingly being scrapped.

title: Jacqui Lambie's brutal message to Lidia Thorpe
description: Jacqui Lambie says Lidia Thorpe 'must take responsibility' after nightclub footage

title: Emmanuel Macron will attend King's coronation to show 'friendship, respect and esteem' for Britain
description: It comes after Macron asked the King to cancel the first planned trip of his reign in March over nationwide rioting. The President added that relations with the UK are 'very important'.

title: Porter Davis homes deal struck, hundreds of properties will be completed
description: Another home builder has signed on to complete close to 400 unfinished Porter Davis properties.

title: Katie Price considers legal action after Met Police officers' messages mocking disabled son
description: The model, 44, has said she is 'not going to let it drop' and was considering her options of claims over discrimination and defamation.

title: Former Everton footballer who was arrested on suspicion of child sex offences considers legal action
description: The player, who cannot be named for legal reasons, was arrested in July 2021 at his home, which he shares with family. He was reportedly arrested after a complaint was made relating to a young girl.

title: Just 13 of 150 emergency laybys promised by government to make smart motorways safer built
description: Currently, emergency laybys are as far apart as 1.5 miles on several stretches of the controversial smart motorways, despite ministers promising 150 to make roads safer.

title: Dales Campground, Karijini National Park: Mum fights off dingo as it attacks son, two
description: A mother has bravely fought off a dingo that attacked and injured her two-year-old son at a remote national park in Western Australia.

title: New Zealand crash horror: Six people killed in incidents in Geraldine, Waikato Expy, Dargaville
description: New Zealand has experienced a horror morning on its roads, with six people killed in three separate crashes.

title: Drummoyne teenager missing as police search for 15-year-old Sydney girl
description: Katia Di Palma, 15, was last seen leaving her home at Drummoyne, in Sydney's inner west, at 6pm on Saturday.

title: Four killed in Alabama mass shooting at Sweet 16 party where 28 people were injured
description: At least four people have died and another 28 have been injured at a Sweet 16 birthday party in a small-town in Alabama.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: End the horror of hospital sex attacks
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: The revelation that at least 6,539 rapes and sexual assaults, some against children, have been committed in infirmaries in just four years is truly horrific.

title: Road rage driver appears to deliberately mow down cyclist in Pakenham, Melbourne
description: A 59-year-old male cyclist has been hit by a car in an alleged hit and run incident in Pakenham, southeast of Melboune, on Thursday, where he suffered bruises and grazes and was taken to hospital.

title: Convictions for sex offences fell sharply on Keir Starmer's watch
description: Just 55 per cent of those charged with sex crimes were convicted in 2013, in Sir Keir Starmer's final year as Head of the Crown Prosecution Service, it has emerged.

title:
LIZ HOGGARD: Can Michelle Obama's 
exercise class cure my gymphobia?
description: My exercise coach, Louis, reassures me, 'Don't worry. This isn't going to be a beasting,' as he straps a heart-rate monitor to my arm.

title: Germany shuts down its last three nuclear power plants
description: Germany has shut down its last three nuclear power plants as part of a long-planned transition. The closure, which was agreed more than a decade ago, is being closely watched abroad.

title: Hume Highway crash leaves woman dead after ute collides with hatchback north of Goulburn
description: A woman has died after the hatchback she was driving collided with utilty vehicle on the Hume Highway at Boxers creek, about 10km northeast of Goulburn, on Monday morning.

title: Pictured: Man, 20, who was stabbed outside a Tube station and died in a London shop
description: Filipe was attacked outside Tulse Hill in south London on Saturday around 6pm. He was found wounded inside a shop along busy Norwood Road. No arrests have been made at this time.

title: ANDREW PIERCE: Has the Penny finally dropped on the trans issue?
description: ANDREW PIERCE: Mordaunt's two Tory leadership campaigns were badly damaged by her past declaration that 'trans women are women', as well as her reference to 'pregnant people'.
